12. dxe6 $18 {White is clearly better.} Nxa1 {Diagram [#] Nielsen,Peter Heine:
'!' Nielsen,Peter Heine: 'As the structure has changed dramatically this back
and forth, is fully justified. The bishop now supports ...f5 and the b7-square
perhaps surpringly is very useful for the black knight, in terms of blockading
the queenside structure as we will later see.' Nielsen,Peter Heine: 'Da sich
die Struktur dramatisch verändert hat, ist dieses Hin und Her völlig
gerechtfertigt. Der Läufer unterstützt nun ...f5 und das Feld b7 ist
vielleicht überraschend nützlich für den schwarzen Springer, um die
Struktur am Damenflügel zu blockieren, wie wir später sehen werden.'} 13.
exf7+ $146 {[%eval 15,22]} (13. Qe4 $1 $18 {[%eval 170,23][%cal Re4c6]} Na5 14.
exf7+ Kxf7 15. Nc3) 13... Kxf7 $11 {And now ...Qd8-d5 would win.} 14. e6+ $1
Kg8 $1 15. Qe4 {[%mdl 1024] Nielsen,Peter Heine: '?!'. Prevents Qd8-d5. White
has compensation. Nielsen,Peter Heine: '15 a3 was the better move-order as the
computers then want to meet 15...f5 with 16 exf5 and then having the rook on
b1 allows ...Bxf5!? The concept is that after 16...gxf5 17 Rb1 black's attack
on the kingside is less easy to progress than in the game.' Nielsen,Peter
Heine: '15 a3 war die bessere Zugfolge, da die Computer dann 15...f5 mit 16
