1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. Nc3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5 5. e4 Nxc3 6. bxc3 Bg7 7. Bc4 c5 8.
Ne2 O-O 9. O-O Nc6 10. Be3 b6 {10...Bg4 is the modern continuation. 10...Lg4
ist die moderne Fortsetzung.} 11. Qd2 ({Praggnanandhaa had been successful with
} 11. h4 {a few months earlier against Anish Giri, as you can see in the notes
to Mchedlishvili, M - Petriashvili, N Tbilisi 2022, which is analyzed
elsewhere in this month's update.}) 11... Bb7 12. Rac1 e6 ({There are plenty
of similarities between the present game and that of Duda, J - Nepomniachtchi,
I Opera online rapid 2021, where} 12... Rc8 13. Rfd1 e6 {occurred, see the
archives for a comparison.}) 13. f3 {Flear,Glenn: 'A sensible move just
protecting the e4-pawn, thus tidying up. However, (for theory purists out
there who want to know!) I have to admit that there doesn't seem to be any
objective pull from here.'} Rc8 ({Various other moves seem to lead to equality:
} 13... Qe7 14. Rfd1 Rfd8 15. Bg5 {(a slight inconvenience for Black who does
well to avoid the weakening 15...f6)} Bf6 16. h4 h5 17. Qf4 {(the most forcing)
} Bxg5 18. Qxg5 Qxg5 19. hxg5 Rac8 {Molina, R - Dounis, A Titled Tuesday
online blitz 2021, and Black is solid enough.}) (13... cxd4 14. cxd4 Na5 15.
Bd3 Rc8 16. Rxc8 Qxc8 17. Rc1 (17. h4 Nc4 $132) 17... Qd7 18. h4 Rc8 19. h5
Rxc1+ 20. Qxc1 Qc6 21. hxg6 (21. h6 Qxc1+ 22. Bxc1 {and now f6 or f8, but not
h8 for the bishop}) 21... hxg6 22. Kf2 Qxc1 23. Bxc1 Nc6 24. Bb2 Kf8 25. Ke3
Ke8 {Vardan, N - Kovchan, A Novi Sad 2022, and a draw was soon agreed.}) 14. h4
{Flear,Glenn: 'A gambit, daring the opponent to snatch a 'warm' pawn.'} ({
Routine play doesn't lead very far:} 14. Rfd1 cxd4 15. cxd4 Qd6 16. Bh6 (16. h4
{is more testing}) 16... Bxh6 17. Qxh6 Na5 18. Bd3 Rxc1 19. Qxc1 Rc8 20. Qd2 (
