Masters 2018. With that in mind the text is kind of forced to protect the
knight although it's worth remembering that the steed can return to e4 in the
future whilst ...fxe4 fxe4 would leave the black d5-knight pinned to his king.}
) 17... h6 ({Interesting is that the engine does prefer White slightly after} 
17... Rb8 {either with 18 Bb3 covering the b2-pawn or 18 Bxa7 greedily
grabbing a pawn. Nevertheless in practical play Black has only lost once in 17
