Black surviving here in practice.} Nb4 $2 {doesn't work due to} 16. a3 Ne4 17.
Nxe4 Rxc2 18. Nxd6+ $18) 13. O-O-O g5 $1 $132 {gives Black very decent
counterplay.}) (11... d5 $1 12. O-O-O O-O-O {transposes to 11...0-0-0!}) 12.
O-O-O {is Gawain's mainline.} (12. a3 Bxd3 13. Qxd3 Qf5 14. Rd1 {D.
Khismatullin - A.Sarana, Yaroslavl 2019 (0-1 in 55).} Qxd3 15. Rxd3 Rhe8 $11 {
is fine for Black, as noted by Sam in the archives.}) 12... d5 $1 {Black's
best try.} (12... Kb8 13. Kb1 Rhe8 14. a3 $5 e5 (14... Bg7 15. Rhe1 $14 {
looks very harmonious for White.}) 15. Bxf5 gxf5 16. Qe1 Bg7 17. Nd5 Qxe1 18.
Rhxe1 $14 {gives White nice pressure against Black's weakened central pawns.})
(12... e5 13. Bxf5+ gxf5 14. Qe1 $1 {This manoeuvre is well-worth keeping in
