Nxh3 O-O-O 14. Rhe1 d5 $17 {is a clear extra pawn for Black.}) 11. Bg2 {
1/2 (40)-1/2 (40) Fedoseev,V (2704)-Wojtaszek,R (2686) Berlin GER 2022} Bg4 $1
12. Nge2 Qa5 13. Nxe4 Qxd2+ 14. Rxd2 Nxe4 15. Bxe4 O-O-O $11 {is very
comfortable for Black.}) 10... Qa5 ({Gawain only covers} 10... fxe4 $2 {
here, giving} 11. h3 $1 {as an improvement over his own game against Donchenko.
This has also been tested in practice:} (11. Kb1 Qa5 $1 (11... Be6 12. h3 Qa5
13. g4 Bg7 14. Bg2 d5 15. g5 $1 Nh5 16. Nxd5 Qxd2 17. Rxd2 $16 {White is doing
well here as Black's King is much worse-placed on e8 than on g8.}) 12. h3 (12.
a3 $5 $146 {Another Gawain suggestion.} Be6 $5 (12... g5 $2 13. b4 $1 Qf5 14.
