Qc2 f5 $15 {Black has a very easy game now.} (15... Qh4 16. f4 Bxh3 $5) 16.
exf5 (16. f3 f4 17. Bf2 h5 $40) 16... Bxf5 17. Qc1 Bd3 (17... Ne4 18. Bf3 Qh4
$15) 18. Bg5 (18. Bxd3 Nxd3 19. Qd2 Nc5 20. f4 $11) 18... Qd7 19. Qe3 Bxe2 20.
Qxe2 Qf5 21. Bh6 Rf6 22. f4 Qd3 23. Rae1 Qxe2 24. Rxe2 Nd3 25. g3 {The
activity of the white pieces compensate his double pawns.} exf4 26. gxf4 Rf5
27. Re3 Nb2 28. Re7 Rf7 29. Rfe1 Rxe7 30. Rxe7 Nxc4 (30... Rc8 $11) 31. Kf2 (
31. Rxc7 Ne3 32. c4 Nf5 33. Bg5 $11) 31... b5 $6 (31... Rc8 $11) 32. Rg7+ Kh8
33. Rxc7 Nb6 34. Bg7+ Kg8 35. Bd4 Nxd5 36. Rg7+ Kf8 37. Rxh7 Re8 38. Kf3 a5 39.
Ra7 (39. Rd7 Re6 40. Ra7 $16) 39... b4 40. c4 Ne7 41. Rxa5 Rc8 42. Bf6 Rxc4 43.
